  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "1Q4D0yxgOzJI4chVBUWLBFgT3nE=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# Bee Node Prerequisites and Dev Mode Constraints\n\nThe adapter requires a running Bee node (v2.7.1+ recommended), a funded postage stamp of depth 22+ (~7.7 GB capacity), and an Ethereum wallet for key derivation.\n\nTests run against `bee dev` \u2014 a memory-only Bee node with no blockchain and no real tokens:\n\n- Full HTTP API on port 1633\n- Postage stamps work but are free\n- Data is stored in memory only (lost on restart)\n- **SOC/Feeds are not supported in dev mode** \u2014 the adapter automatically falls back to `/bytes` mode when it detects dev\n\nThis dev-mode `/bytes`-only fallback is a meaningful behavioral branch: the mutable-feed pointer pattern that powers production recovery does not actually exercise in dev tests; only the immutable upload path is covered.\n\nA test stamp can be minted with:\n\n```bash\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:1633/stamps/10000000/24 | jq .batchID\n```\n\nThe 12 E2E tests live in the adapter package and require `bee dev` running in a separate terminal before `pnpm test`.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
    }
  },
